content: Today, I want to analyze one game about i6 opening.
i6 opening is the first opening we learned in new theory lessons.
What's your opinion about this opening?
i can even lose it with black :-D
I am very glad to hear that black win
that would make the lesson easier:)
i maybe like to ues white
i6 opening was an opening full with tricky moves.
but please do move so quick,that would leave me behind
Without good analysis and careful preparation, It is very difficult to find sure win in fast games.
That's the reason why there are still some top players used this gambling opening in top tournament.
i6 opening is too hard to learn,i think
We all know that Chingin was sucessful with i6 opening in WC-8
how many people could know all win branches in the world?
We studied i6 opening in new theory department in last year
one more year past, maybe some old variants solved, but new variants appeared
It maybe interesting for us to fresh our memory in analyze lesson:)
that's why I choose this game
why do we call this a i-6 opening?
The game played between two of our classmates
ASV777 chose the opening and moocheng swapped
g9 and g10 are the two 5th moves
g10 the main and g9 the alternative one
there are two 7th moves here, 7-f10 and 7-j7
heard that G9 black have been clear now
what's your opinion about 7-f10? Is it black sure win?
good, that makes my job easier:)
In theory lesson, GM scm2000 showed variants after 8-e11
oh f10 sure win?i just heard j7 win
that's what we studied in theory lesson
who want to show win here?
a good supplement to theory lessons
so we can see that this 7th move gives black satisfying result
but we can also find that, it is such a long variant
I think not easy to find all win of 14th, in 20 minutes game
maybe moocheng dont know this way
so we can see that he chose anothor 7
one of good outcome of this 7 is that
white cannot defense at i7 now
before we go to that, how about this 14?

What's the intension of this move?

to see one of the outcome first
if white block the pair from g6
After 18->G6,I have No idea at once
here, moocheng maybe confused about the development moves
I think it is because of the f9 point taken by white

I think white can defend from both side
black choose to develop at lower side
we check some active white moves first
now we can see how 25 help black
so white cannot be too active when 26th move
and asv777 took the good chance to take j6 away
j6 is the key point for black to connect the lower materials
just to try to use tempo to gain more help for future defence
kill all black potential at the left-lower cornor
if 45 defend at f4, white win in right side
if 45 up, white win in left side
but give black more chance to survive
but still white win at last
this is how the game ended
We are so glad to find that,
black has sure win after 6th move
